      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\SOPs\\SOP-009-TV-Dashboard-Setup.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # SOP-009: TV Dashboard Setup\n2: \n3: **Version:** 1.0  \n4: **Date:** 05 July 2026  \n5: **Author:** Andrea Enning (AndieKobbieTech)\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: This SOP describes how to set up a Samsung Smart TV dashboard that displays real-time glucose data, alerts, and daily summaries.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Prerequisites\n16: \n17: | Item | Requirement |\n18: |------|-------------|\n19: | **Hardware** | Samsung 55\" Smart TV, PC on same network |\n20: | **Software** | Web browser on TV |\n21: | **Data** | Nightscout server (SOP-007) |\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: PC (Nightscout) → TV Browser → Glucose Dashboard\n29:          ↓\n30:     Voice Alerts (via TV speakers)\n31: ```\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## Procedure\n36: \n37: ### Step 1: Create Dashboard HTML\n38: \n39: Create `tv_dashboard.html`:\n40: ```html\n41: <!DOCTYPE html>\n42: <html>\n43: <head>\n44:     <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n45:     <meta http-equiv=\"refresh\" content=\"300\"> <!-- Refresh every 5 minutes -->\n46:     <title>Glucose Dashboard</title>\n47:     <style>\n48:         body { \n49:             font-family: Arial; \n50:             background: #1a1a2e; \n51:             color: white; \n52:             text-align: center;\n53:             padding: 50px;\n54:         }\n55:         .glucose { font-size: 120px; }\n56:         .status { font-size: 40px; }\n57:         .time { font-size: 30px; color: #888; }\n58:         .normal { color: #00ff00; }\n59:         .high { color: #ffff00; }\n60:         .low { color: #ff0000; }\n61:     </style>\n62: </head>\n63: <body>\n64:     <div class=\"time\" id=\"time\"></div>\n65:     <div class=\"glucose\" id=\"glucose\">--</div>\n66:     <div class=\"status\" id=\"status\">Loading...</div>\n67:     <script>\n68:         async function update() {\n69:             const res = await fetch('http://YOUR-PC-IP:1337/api/v1/entries.json?count=1');\n70:             const data = await res.json();\n71:             if (data.length > 0) {\n72:                 const bg = data[0].sgv / 18;\n73:                 document.getElementById('glucose').textContent = bg.toFixed(1);\n74:                 document.getElementById('glucose').className = 'glucose ' + \n75:                     (bg < 4 ? 'low' : bg > 10 ? 'high' : 'normal');\n76:                 document.getElementById('status').textContent = \n77:                     bg < 4 ? '⚠️ LOW' : bg > 10 ? '⚠️ HIGH' : '✅ Normal';\n78:             }\n79:             document.getElementById('time').textContent = new Date().toLocaleTimeString();\n80:         }\n81:         update();\n82:         setInterval(update, 60000);\n83:     </script>\n84: </body>\n85: </html>\n86: ```\n87: \n88: ### Step 2: Host Dashboard\n89: \n90: ```powershell\n91: cd ~/agentson/viewers/web\n92: python -m http.server 8080\n93: ```\n94: \n95: ### Step 3: Find PC's IP\n96: \n97: ```powershell\n98: ipconfig | findstr \"IPv4\"\n99: ```\n100: \n101: ### Step 4: Open on TV\n102: \n103: 1. Turn on Samsung TV\n104: 2. Open built-in web browser\n105: 3. Enter: `http://YOUR-PC-IP:8080/tv_dashboard.html`\n106: 4. Bookmark for easy access\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: ## TV Browser Tips\n111: \n112: | Tip | How |\n113: |-----|-----|\n114: | **Full screen** | Press F11 or TV's full screen button |\n115: | **Auto-refresh** | HTML refreshes every 5 minutes |\n116: | **Font size** | Adjust CSS for TV viewing distance |\n117: | **Color coding** | Green=normal, Yellow=high, Red=low |\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: ## Voice Alerts via TV\n122: \n123: If TV has Alexa or built-in speakers:\n124: \n125: 1. **Enable screen reader** in TV settings\n126: 2. **Use text-to-speech** for critical alerts\n127: 3. **Play audio files** via TV's media player\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ## Troubleshooting\n132: \n133: | Issue | Solution |\n134: |-------|----------|\n135: | TV can't connect | Check same WiFi network |\n136: | Dashboard not loading | Check PC IP, firewall settings |\n137: | Data not updating | Check Nightscout server running |\n138: | Font too small | Increase CSS font-size |\n\n(End of file - total 138 lines)\n</content>",
