      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentSON\n2: \n3: **Agent + JSON** — Yet Another JSON, but metadata-rich and built for the agentic era.\n4: \n5: ## What's in a Name\n6: \n7: | Component | Meaning |\n8: |-----------|---------|\n9: | **Agent** | AI coding agents (Cursor, Claude Code, opencode, MiniMax, etc.) |\n10: | **SON** | JSON — the format it's built on |\n11: \n12: Like **JSON** itself — which was \"just another data format\" but became universal because it was simple, readable, and worked everywhere — **AgentSON** is \"just another JSON\" but designed specifically for the agentic era.\n13: \n14: **AgentSON = Agent + JSON**\n15: \n16: It's immediately recognizable (everyone knows JSON), signals the format (it IS JSON with a schema), and differentiates from \"yet another format\" to \"the JSON for agents.\"\n17: \n18: ## The Problem\n19: \n20: Every AI coding agent stores session data in its own proprietary SQLite database:\n21: \n22: | Tool | Database | Tables | Schema |\n23: |------|----------|--------|--------|\n24: | opencode | `opencode.db` | 21 | session, message, part, todo |\n25: | MiniMax | `sqlite.db` | 20 | sessions, session_messages |\n26: | Antigravity IDE | `*.db` | 7 | trajectory_meta, steps |\n27: | Chrome DevTools AI | Preferences JSON | — | user-query, thought, action |\n28: \n29: **Nobody has done for agent session logs what OpenAPI did for REST APIs.**\n30: \n31: ## The Solution\n32: \n33: AgentSON provides:\n34: \n35: 1. **A specification** — JSON Schema for agent session data\n36: 2. **Readers** — SQLite parsers for each tool's database\n37: 3. **A normalizer** — Converts tool-specific schemas to AgentSON format\n38: 4. **A CLI** — Export, search, and render sessions\n39: 5. **A VSCode extension** — Hydrate context across tools\n40: \n41: ## File Extension\n42: \n43: AgentSON files use the `.AgentSON` extension:\n44: \n45: ```\n46: my-session.AgentSON\n47: ```\n48: \n49: This makes them:\n50: - **Immediately identifiable** — not `.json` (too generic), not `.ailog` (old name)\n51: - **Grep-friendly** — `grep -r \"nightscout\" *.AgentSON`\n52: - **Tool-associated** — can be associated with the AgentSON CLI or viewer\n53: - **Windows-friendly** — `.agentson` (lowercase) also works on Windows\n54: \n55: ## Quick Start\n56: \n57: ```bash\n58: # Install\n59: pip install -e .\n60: \n61: # Or from GitHub\n62: pip install git+https://github.com/andiekobbietks/AgentSON.git\n63: \n64: # List opencode sessions\n65: agentson list --tool opencode\n66: \n67: # Export a session\n68: agentson export --tool opencode --session ses_xxx --output ./sessions/\n69: \n70: # Export all sessions\n71: agentson export --tool opencode --all --output ./sessions/\n72: \n73: # Render as Markdown\n74: agentson render session.AgentSON --format md\n75: \n76: # Export training data (Unsloth/ShareGPT format)\n77: agentson finetune *.AgentSON --format unsloth --output train.jsonl\n78: \n79: # Export training data (Olive format)\n80: agentson finetune *.AgentSON --format olive --output train.jsonl\n81: \n82: # Push to Supabase (optional)\n83: agentson push session.AgentSON\n84: \n85: # Pull from Supabase\n86: agentson pull --search \"nightscout\"\n87: ```\n88: \n89: > **Note:** On Windows, if `agentson` command isn't found after install, use `python -m cli.main` instead.\n90: \n91: ## Schema\n92: \n93: ```json\n94: {\n95:   \"$schema\": \"https://agentson.dev/schema/v1.json\",\n96:   \"id\": \"session-2026-07-04-001\",\n97:   \"tool\": {\"name\": \"opencode\", \"session_id\": \"ses_xxx\"},\n98:   \"agent\": {\"name\": \"mimo-v2.5-free\", \"provider\": \"opencode\"},\n99:   \"entries\": [\n100:     {\"type\": \"user-query\", \"text\": \"...\"},\n101:     {\"type\": \"thought\", \"text\": \"...\"},\n102:     {\"type\": \"action\", \"tool\": \"bash\", \"code\": \"...\", \"output\": \"...\"},\n103:     {\"type\": \"answer\", \"text\": \"...\"},\n104:     {\"type\": \"side-effect\", \"action\": \"file_write\", \"path\": \"...\"}\n105:   ]\n106: }\n107: ```\n108: \n109: ## Entry Types\n110: \n111: | Type | Description |\n112: |------|-------------|\n113: | `user-query` | User's input or question |\n114: | `context` | Additional context (data used, DOM info) |\n115: | `querying` | Agent is processing |\n116: | `title` | Section or step title |\n117: | `thought` | Agent's reasoning/thinking |\n118: | `action` | Tool execution (code + output) |\n119: | `answer` | Agent's response |\n120: | `side-effect` | File changes, state mutations |\n121: \n122: ## Supported Tools\n123: \n124: | Tool | Status | Reader |\n125: |------|--------|--------|\n126: | opencode | ✅ Working | `readers/opencode.py` |\n127: | MiniMax | ✅ Working | `readers/minimax.py` |\n128: | Antigravity IDE | ✅ Working | `readers/antigravity.py` |\n129: | Chrome DevTools AI | ⚠️ Unknown storage | JS snippet (experimental) |\n130: | Cursor | 🔜 Planned | — |\n131: | Claude Code | 🔜 Planned | — |\n132: \n133: ### Chrome DevTools AI Status\n134: \n135: Chrome DevTools AI stores session data in an unknown location. The `ai_assistance: {}` field in Preferences JSON is empty, despite extensive usage visible in screenshots. The actual storage mechanism remains unclear — possibly cloud sync or different local storage.\n136: \n137: ## Use Cases\n138: \n139: ### For Individuals\n140: - Search your AI history: `grep -r \"smtpjs\" *.AgentSON`\n141: - Resume sessions in different tools\n142: - Backup that survives tool changes\n143: - Personal training data for fine-tuning\n144: \n145: ### For Teams\n146: - Audit trail of AI-generated code\n147: - Onboarding: ship new devs your session archive\n148: - Knowledge persistence across team changes\n149: \n150: ### For Agent Builders\n151: - Standardized eval datasets\n152: - Real session traces for fine-tuning\n153: - Tool-use analysis across agents\n154: \n155: ## Fine-Tuning Export\n156: \n157: Export AgentSON sessions to training formats:\n158: \n159: ```bash\n160: # Unsloth/ShareGPT format (for LLaMA, Mistral, etc.)\n161: agentson finetune *.AgentSON --format unsloth --output train.jsonl\n162: \n163: # Olive format (Microsoft Olive pipeline)\n164: agentson finetune *.AgentSON --format olive --output train.jsonl\n165: ```\n166: \n167: Example output (Unsloth format):\n168: ```json\n169: {\n170:   \"conversations\": [\n171:     {\"from\": \"human\", \"value\": \"How do I fix the auth bug?\"},\n172:     {\"from\": \"gpt\", \"value\": \"I'll look at the auth module...\"}\n173:   ],\n174:   \"source\": \"opencode\",\n175:   \"session_id\": \"ses_xxx\"\n176: }\n177: ```\n178: \n179: ## PWA Viewer\n180: \n181: The `pwa/` directory contains a standalone Progressive Web App for viewing `.AgentSON` files:\n182: \n183: 1. Open `pwa/index.html` in a browser\n184: 2. Drag-and-drop an `.AgentSON` file\n185: 3. Browse entries with keyboard navigation\n186: 4. Works offline — no server required\n187: \n188: To host on GitHub Pages, enable Pages for the `pwa/` directory.\n189: \n190: ## Architecture\n191: \n192: ### Two-Layer Design\n193: \n194: | Layer | What | Like |\n195: |-------|------|------|\n196: | **Open Spec** | `.AgentSON` file format | Dev Containers — portable, file-based, works offline |\n197: | **Managed Instance** | Supabase backend | GitHub — sync, search, collaboration |\n198: \n199: ```\n200: Git (local, file-based) → GitHub (cloud, collaboration)\n201: AgentSON (file-based) → AgentSON Cloud (Supabase)\n202: ```\n203: \n204: ### The Flow\n205: \n206: ```\n207: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n208: │                    AgentSON Architecture                     │\n209: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n210: │                                                             │\n211: │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐        │\n212: │  │   Cursor    │  │ Claude Code │  │   opencode  │        │\n213: │  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘        │\n214: │         │                │                │                  │\n215: │         ▼                ▼                ▼                  │\n216: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n217: │  │         .AgentSON Files (Open Spec)                  │   │\n218: │  │     Portable, vendor-neutral, file-based             │   │\n219: │  └─────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────┘   │\n220: │                             │                                │\n221: │              ┌──────────────┼──────────────┐               │\n222: │              ▼              ▼              ▼               │\n223: │  ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐      │\n224: │  │   Local CLI  │ │   Supabase   │ │  Web Viewer  │      │\n225: │  │  (offline)   │ │  (optional)  │ │   (shared)   │      │\n226: │  └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘      │\n227: │                                                             │\n228: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n229: ```\n230: \n231: ## Repository Structure\n232: \n233: ```\n234: agentson/\n235: ├── README.md              # This file\n236: ├── PRD.md                 # Full product requirements\n237: ├── PERSONAS-AND-USER-STORIES.md  # User personas and stories\n238: ├── pyproject.toml         # Python packaging (pip install -e .)\n239: ├── setup.py               # Backward-compat shim\n240: ├── spec/\n241: │   └── v1.json            # JSON Schema\n242: ├── readers/               # Tool-specific readers\n243: │   ├── opencode.py        # ✅ Working\n244: │   ├── minimax.py         # ✅ Working\n245: │   ├── antigravity.py     # ✅ Working\n246: │   └── libre.py           # ✅ Working (FreeStyle Libre 2)\n247: ├── importers/             # External format importers\n248: │   └── chatgpt.py         # ✅ ChatGPT conversations.json\n249: ├── exporters/             # Training data exporters\n250: │   └── finetune.py        # ✅ Unsloth + Olive formats\n251: ├── normalizer/            # Schema conversion (planned)\n252: ├── renderers/             # Output formats (planned)\n253: ├── cli/                   # Command-line interface\n254: │   ├── main.py            # ✅ Working\n255: │   └── supabase_client.py # ✅ Working\n256: ├── supabase/              # Managed instance schema\n257: ├── tests/                 # Test suite\n258: │   ├── test_opencode.py   # ✅ Passing\n259: │   ├── test_minimax.py    # ✅ Passing\n260: │   └── test_antigravity.py # ✅ Passing\n261: ├── examples/              # Example .AgentSON files\n262: │   ├── opencode_example.AgentSON\n263: │   ├── minimax_example.AgentSON\n264: │   └── antigravity_example.AgentSON\n265: ├── pwa/                   # Progressive Web App viewer\n266: │   ├── index.html         # ✅ Drag-and-drop viewer\n267: │   ├── manifest.json      # ✅ PWA manifest\n268: │   └── sw.js              # ✅ Service worker\n269: ├── viewers/\n270: │   └── web/index.html     # ✅ Working (drag-and-drop viewer)\n271: ├── training/\n272: │   └── opencode_example_unsloth.jsonl  # Example training data\n273: └── docs/\n274:     └── sops/              # 14 Standard Operating Procedures\n275: ```\n276: \n277: ## Origin\n278: \n279: AgentSON evolved from `.ailog` — a format originally designed for Chrome DevTools AI session export. The schema was discovered in Chrome's Preferences JSON and generalized to cover all AI coding agents.\n280: \n281: The name \"AgentSON\" is a play on JSON — **Agent + JSON** — \"Yet Another JSON\" but metadata-rich and built for the agentic era.\n282: \n283: ### What Changed from .ailog\n284: \n285: | Aspect | .ailog | AgentSON |\n286: |--------|--------|----------|\n287: | Scope | Chrome DevTools only | All AI coding agents |\n288: | Schema | Undocumented | JSON Schema v1 |\n289: | File extension | `.ailog` | `.AgentSON` |\n290: | Name meaning | AI Log | Agent + JSON |\n291: \n292: See [PRD.md](PRD.md) for the full product requirements document.\n293: \n294: ## License\n295: \n296: MIT\n297: \n298: ---\n299: \n300: *\"Nobody has done for agent session logs what OpenAPI did for REST APIs or what containers.dev did for dev environments.\"*\n\n(End of file - total 300 lines)\n</content>",
